B59635.title: SFU Peak Frequency
B59635.description: To provide performance opportunities for student musicians and foster a musical environment where people can socialize and share a common interest.

01DFE8.title: SFU Pokemon Go Official Group
01DFE8.description: Official campus trade/pvp/raid group! Doesn't matter what team you are on, come meet other players in the SFU community!

A50312.title: SFU Polyglots
A50312.description: aims to provide a casual and friendly environment for students to meet and discuss all things related to languages, including language acquisition, and language exchange, with fellow members of the SFU community.

3DC6CC.title: SFU Pre-Dental Society
3DC6CC.description: Our club focuses on informing students interested in pursuing a future in dentistry on the application process; DAT, the pre-requisites, current entrance statistics, and various other qualities looked for in potential candidates, to inform as many students of as many possibilities open to them in the future.

EEFDEE.title: SFU Real Estate Club
EEFDEE.description: The  is a student led organization that allows students to be exposed to the real estate world through events and projects. Our vision is to create a community amongst the students interested in real estate and help them grow their network within the industry.

075EBA.title: SFU Robot Soccer
075EBA.description:
club aims to combine the excitement of soccer with the future of automated technology as we compete in RoboCup. Our team encourages students from all programs to learn concepts that are not taught in class and get hands-on experience with robotics, artificial intelligence, and teamwork.

Join our Discord via: linktr.ee/sfurs

A19E5A.title: SFU Robotics Club
A19E5A.description: SFU students that are interested in learning about robotics and/or participating in robotics related activities (ex. competitions)

356DC6.title: SFU Rocketry
356DC6.description: To research, design, and build rockets to compete in rocketry competitions and further the understanding and competency of SFU students in the field of engineering.

1DE076.title: SFU Sports Analytics Club
1DE076.description: Where data and sports come together. We aim to connect individuals interested in sports, data, or analysis to share ideas and opinions. As data is more prevalent and publicly available than ever, we promote the importance of usage of data to investigate sports-related issues in the light of improving performance and strategies.

A38833.title: SFU Surge
A38833.description: We are a community for students in tech to learn from industry professionals at conferences and talks, to hone skills and experience at large-scale hackathons and competitions, to network at events and workshops to enable community innovation, and to gain project experience working on software used by SFU students.

2BB838.title: SFU Swifties
2BB838.description:
A club for fans of music to talk about anything and everything with a shared interest in Taylor Swift's music and projects :)

For timely updates and announcements, please follow our instagram page or Discord server (located on the linktree website)

F19ED5.title: SFU Thaqalyn Muslim Association
F19ED5.description: As a collective, TMA SFU aims to embody and promote the values of the Quran, the Holy Prophet PBUH and his holy Household within our society and on campus, as we prepare for the reappearance of the Imam of our time. In addition, we hope to provide an inclusive, supportive and accepting environment for Muslim students at Simon Fraser University.

1316D9.title: SFU Transit Enthusiasts Club (SFU TEC)
1316D9.description: Welcome to the ! Join us for discussions about Public Transit in Metro Vancouver and the world, and even for some urban planning too! Most of our discussion takes place on our discord server, but we do have in-person meetings once a month!

0954C1.title: SFUnison
0954C1.description: is SFU's a cappella group. Have you always wanted to make music, but felt tied down by the thought of committing to playing an instrument? All you need to bring is your voice! We are open to all skill levels!

FBF4E5.title: Sikh Students' Association - SFU
FBF4E5.description: Establish a strong network for those who are exploring the Sikh way of life. We hope to achieve this by promoting Sikh values such as equality, peace and truthful living in order to create a strong and united Sikh community at Simon Fraser University.

D869C1.title: Ski and Snowboard Club
D869C1.description: The Ski and Snowboard club is focused on bringing together the SFU shred community, regardless of abilities on the slopes! We're just a group of gnarly people looking for more gnarly people to be gnarly with! If you're looking for good times, and to make some turns on the slopes this season, this club is for you!

783B2D.title: Smash Club
783B2D.description: To provide a place for students to play the popular video game franchise Super Smash Bros., both competitively and casually.

2A6250.title: Speech and Hearing Club
2A6250.description: This club is for prospective Speech-Language Pathologists and Audiologists who want to maximize their ability to get into graduate school.

282193.title: STEM Fellowship
282193.description: Non-profit organization at SFU that strives to engage future leaders and innovators in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics.

F12A17.title: Student Marketing Association
F12A17.description:
The  (SMA) is SFU’s creative and innovative marketing-based student club. Students from all faculties join together in this organization to gain skills in marketing, event coordination, and leadership, planning numerous social and professional events throughout the year. 


Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/sfusma/

Linkedin: https://www.linkedin.com/company/sfu-student-marketing-association

Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/SFUStudentMarketingAssociation

4E1963.title: Surrey Badminton Club - SFU
4E1963.description: The Surrey Badminton Club promotes Badminton to all SFU Students, particularly at SFU Surrey Campus. This club welcomes any skill level/gender and will enforce a safe zone for all participants.

1A80D6.title: Tabletop
1A80D6.description: is a club dedicated to building a safe, accessible, and welcoming community where students can play board games, roleplaying games, and many other tabletop games together.

5600C3.title: Taiwanese Association - SFU
5600C3.description: SFUTA was established in 1989, We are the bridge between Canada and Taiwan. We are a social and cultural club that promotes an engaging university experience. SFUTA成立於1989年，我們是加拿大和台灣之間的橋樑。我們是一個多元文化社團，旨在促進學生參與大學的生活體驗。

1AE75D.title: Tamil Student Association  (TSA)
1AE75D.description: To be a safe space where students affiliated with the Tamil language, culture and heritage, can come together to provide opportunities to bring both Tamils and non-Tamils together.

DF8E15.title: Team Phantom: SFU Formula SAE Electric
DF8E15.description: The goal of this club is to compete in the Formula SAE Electric Competition. The club will do this by designing and creating a fully electric vehicle using engineering principles.

369D35.title: The FentaNIL Project at SFU (TFP)
369D35.description:
The FentaNIL Project (TFP) is dedicated to reducing the impact of the opioid crisis by educating students about harm reduction and how they can help others who are struggling with addiction. We will teach the public how to recognize and respond to overdoses by recommending students obtain naloxone kits. IG: @fentanilsfu
Contact: cog@sfu.ca

F0C678.title: The Point
F0C678.description: A club on campus whose goal is to Love God, Love People, Serve All, by hosting events open to those part of  Church and to those who are not.  Through worship and service, we aim to foster a positive atmosphere on campus where students can explore what it means to follow Jesus.

6CB924.title: Thé SFU Tea
6CB924.description: We aim to encourage and maintain the appreciation of tea in all forms.

D83018.title: Ukrainian Student Society
D83018.description: wants to celebrate Ukrainian identity, culture, and language. We also want to bring awareness about russian aggression and aid Ukraine to help to win the battle for liberty and freedom.

7071C7.title: UNICEF - SFU
7071C7.description: Our focus is to advocate, educate, and fundraise to join the global effort of reversing child-focused humanitarian issues in the developing world.

FBCF34.title: University Bible Fellowship
FBCF34.description: To help students study the Bible and live according to its teachings.

A3FB3F.title: University Christian Ministries
A3FB3F.description: UCM SFU is a Christian community of students at Simon Fraser University. We exist to know and love God, love one another, care for all of our campuses, and tell others about Jesus.

7C448A.title: UPhoto Photography Club
7C448A.description: Everyone who is interested in photography is welcome to join UPhoto. You don't have to be a professional photographer or own a fancy camera to participate in our events. Our goal is simple: to provide those who are interested in photography a platform to have fun and to learn skills from others!

D2B1FA.title: Variety for Tomorrow - SFU
D2B1FA.description: We host events throughout the year to fundraise on behalf of Variety - the Children’s Charity. All of our proceeds support children with special needs in British Columbia. We also offer the opportunity to volunteer at some of Variety’s events, such as the Show of Hearts Telethon, Boat for Hope and their Christmas parties.

8BE77A.title: VeggieSFU
8BE77A.description:
To create a welcoming space for people to explore plant-based diets, seek advice, and have open discussion pertaining to plant-based diets and sustainability. As a member, you can expect restaurant socials, access to recipes and resources, and a place to meet others with common interests.
This club is open to everyone, plant-based or not.

CDBD9F.title: Vietnamese Student Association
CDBD9F.description: An official group for all Vietnamese students and all those who are interested in Vietnamese culture at Simon Fraser University.

59CB9C.title: Vocal Jazz- SFU
59CB9C.description: To spread musical joy throughout the SFU campus.

7F1E69.title: Women in Clean Tech
7F1E69.description:
(WiCT) is an all-inclusive club aiming to connect students in STEM, as well as facilitate clean tech initiatives and projects for our club members. Follow @wict_sfu on Instagram for all updates!
While the focus of this club is to connect and support the women student body interested in this field, all are welcome to join.

04C75C.title: Women In Engineering
04C75C.description: Women in Engineering club stands for diversity, inclusion, and representation of minorities in engineering. We are a club that aims to empower women in STEM through events with a focus toward outreach, support, and career development.

14C005.title: Women in STEM
14C005.description: (WiSTEM) is allied with all students of different backgrounds and identities to create a supportive environment in all fields of STEM. Our main focus is to connect with women through various outreach and networking environments (e.g., study sessions, panels, mixers). This club is open to everyone to join.

F9E0F2.title: Young Women in Business SFU
F9E0F2.description:
YWiB SFU strives to engage leaders from all faculties through opportunities for personal and professional growth. We encourage members to achieve success on their own terms through our programs that focus on mentorship, networking, philanthropy and tangible skill building.
To join YWiB please apply via our website:
www.ywib.ca/sfu/programs
